-- 
Crude, Heating Oil, Gasoline Drop for 2nd Day: Oil Products

-- B y   R i c h a r d   S t u b b e
-- 
2011-04-12T20:18:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/crude-heating-oil-gasoline-drop-for-2nd-day-oil-products.html
Crude oil, gasoline and heating oil
declined for the second day in a row after the  International
Energy Agency  and  International Monetary Fund  said that high
prices are starting to hurt the global economy and  Goldman Sachs
Group Inc. (GS)  forecast a “substantial” correction. Ethanol
slipped the most in four weeks.  Crude Oil  Crude oil for May delivery fell $3.67, or 3.3 percent, to
$106.25 a barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange , extending
the two-day decline to 5.8 percent. Crude has gained 26 percent
in the past year.  U.S. oil supplies probably climbed 1 million barrels last
week from the previous week’s 357.7 million, according to a
Bloomberg News survey of analysts. The Energy Department reports
on stockpiles tomorrow.  Gasoline  Gasoline for May delivery slipped 3.64 cents, or 1.1
percent, to $3.1641 a gallon on the Nymex, the lowest settlement
since April 1. Gasoline has increased 38 percent in a year.  Stockpiles probably dropped 1 million barrels last week
from the previous week’s 217.7 million, according to the
analysts’ median estimate.  Heating Oil  Heating oil for May delivery declined 7.99 cents, or 2.5
percent, to $3.1726 a gallon, a one-week low. Heating oil has
gained 43 percent in a year.  Distillate inventories probably rose 500,000 barrels last
week from the previous 153.5 million barrels, according to the
median analyst estimate.  Ethanol  Denatured ethanol for May delivery fell 7 cents, or 2.6
percent, to $2.66 a gallon on the Chicago Board of Trade, the
lowest settlement since March 31. Ethanol has increased 73
percent in the past year.  Refineries and Transport  A fluid catalytic cracker at  Chevron Corp. (CVX) ’s El Segundo
refinery remained offline as of late yesterday, according to a
person familiar with the plant’s operations. The unit was shut
about a week ago after another unit that provides feed to the
cat cracker malfunctioned and was shut for repairs, according to
the person.  BP Plc restarted a hydrocracker at its Carson refinery in
 California  after planned work, according to a person with
knowledge of the maintenance. The unit was shut in early March
for the work, according to the person.  Valero Energy Corp. (VLO)  is increasing a hydrocracker at its
Port Arthur, Texas, refinery to planned rates,  Bill Day , a
company spokesman, said in an e-mail. A crude unit remains shut
for a repair, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
